Varibles are place holders in order to store some data.

These can be initialized either in the Declaraion Section or in the Execution Section.

Example:-
DECLARE

v_name VARCHAR2(10) := 'Abhinav';

BEGIN

dbms_output.put_line(v_name);

END;

O/P :- Abhinav

---------------------------------------

DECLARE

v_name VARCHAR2(10) := 'Abhinav';

BEGIN
v_name:= 'Abhi';
dbms_output.put_line(v_name);

END;

O/P := Abhi

------------------------------------------
